 (linkOptions parms)‚ÜêProcessLinkOptions(parms config);path;filename;msg;linkconfig
‚çù Looks into the Cider config file and also a file .linkconfig in config.CIDER.source
‚çù If such a file exists and contains more than just the Link version number and "SourceFlags" (that is,
‚çù Stop and Trace vectors), then it takes precedence over what is defined in the (optional) [LINK] section
‚çù of Cider's config file, and the user is told that she should remove any Link-related stuff from Cider's
‚çù config file. If the file .linkconfig exists but carries nothing but stop vectors and trace vectors and
‚çù the Link version number, then a LINK section in the Cider project config file is evaluated but the user
‚çù is told to reconcile the two sources of Link options, and eventaully delete the the LINK section from
‚çù the Cider project config file.
‚çù If .linkconfig does not exist, any Link-specific settings in the Cider config file are evaluated.
 linkOptions‚Üê‚éïNS''
 path‚Üêconfig.CIDER.source{0=‚â¢‚ç∫:‚çµ ‚ãÑ ‚çµ,'/',‚ç∫}parms.folder
 filename‚Üê(F.AddTrailingSep path),'.linkconfig'
 :If F.IsFile filename
     linkconfig‚ÜêGet_JSON5 filename
     ‚çù When there is a file .linkconfig but it does only contain stop vectors and trace vectos (apart from a
     ‚çù Link version number) we carry on as usual: evaluate the LINK section of Cider's project config file.
     :If 9=config.‚éïNC'LINK'
     :AndIf 0<‚â¢config.LINK.‚éïNL‚ç≥16
         :If 0=‚â¢(linkconfig.‚éïNL-2 9)~'LinkVersion' 'SourceFlags'
             :If 0=parms.batch
                 msg‚Üê''
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'There is a file .linkconfig in:'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇF.EnforceSlash path
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'though it contains nothing but stop and trace vectors.'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'The LINK section in the project config file IS evaluated.'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'You are advised to reconcile the two sources of Link options'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'and delete the "LINK" section from Cider''s project config file.'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'Note that Cider''s Linksection were introduced at a time when'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'there was no Link config file available (prior version 4).'
                 ‚çû‚ÜêBox Frame msg
                 ‚çû‚Üê‚éïUCS 10
             :EndIf
         :Else
             :If 0=parms.batch
                 msg‚Üê''
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'There is a file .linkconfig in:'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇF.EnforceSlash path
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'that carries Link options, but there is also a non-empty "LINK"'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'section in Cider''s project config file, which will be IGNORED'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'because of the .linkconfig file.'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'You are advised to delete the "Link" section from Cider''s'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'project config file, maybe after reconciling it with .linkconfig.'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'Note that Cider''s Link options were invented at a time when'
                 msg,‚Üê‚äÇ'there was no Link config file available (prior to version 4).'
                 ‚çû‚ÜêBox Frame msg
                 ‚çû‚Üê‚éïUCS 10
             :EndIf
             linkOptions‚ÜêExtractLinkOptions config             ‚çù Merge the default options with Cider's options
         :EndIf
     :Else
         linkOptions‚ÜêExtractLinkOptions config             ‚çù Merge the default options with Cider's options
     :EndIf
 :EndIf
 :If 0‚â¢parms.watch
 :AndIf 0<config.‚éïNC'LINK'
     config.LINK.watch‚Üêparms.watch           ‚çù Was specified by the user, and that takes (temporarily) precendence
 :ElseIf 2=linkOptions.‚éïNC'watch'
     parms.watch‚ÜêlinkOptions.watch
 :Else
     parms.watch‚Üê(1+HasDotNet)‚äÉ'ns' 'both'   ‚çù Default is "both" but for the time being only when .NET is available
 :EndIf
